<p>And on Monday, LeToya Luckett announced via social media that she has given birth to her second child with husband Tommicus Walker.</p>

<p>Sharing an animated image of a baby's feet on Instagram, the 39-year-old wrote: 'TYSUN WOLF WALKER Overjoyed! Thank you Heavenly Father.'</p>

<p>New arrival: She was a founding member of Destiny's Child. And on Monday, LeToya Luckett announced via social media that she has given birth to her second child</p>

<p>So happy: Sharing an animated image of a baby's feet on Instagram, the 39-year-old singer wrote: 'TYSUN WOLF WALKER Overjoyed! Thank you Heavenly Father'</p>

<p>She added that the baby boy was born at 4:03 a.m. on Monday and weighed in at a healthy nine pounds and seven ounces.</p>

<p>LeToya and Tommicus married in December 2017 in Texas and they welcomed a daughter Gianna in January 2019. </p>

<p>The couple are also parents to Tommicus' daughter Madison from a previous relationship.</p>

<p>LeToya had revealed she was expecting her second child back in March and shared that she was having a boy.</p>

<p>She explained on Instagram: 'In an interest to keep our friends &amp; family safe, <?php echo e('@'); ?>tommicuswalker and I decided against having a gathering to reveal the sex of our little one. Instead, we're choosing to have an online reveal party.' </p>

<p>Baby number 2: LeToya had revealed via Instagram that she was expecting her second child back in March and  at the same time, she shared that she was having a boy</p>

<p>Parents: LeToya shares her son and a daughter Gianna, born in 2019, with husband Tommicus Walker whom she married in December 2017 in Texas (they'r epcitured in September 2019)</p>

<p>LeToya was part of Destiny's Child with Beyonce Knowles, Kelly Rowland and LaTavia Roberson, a group formed by Beyonce's dad Matthew Knowles in 1993.</p>

<p>After the group's first two albums were released and they started to enjoy success, LeToya and LaTavia had a falling out with Knowles and had sought their own representation.</p>

<p>But in the midst of the group's rise to stardom in 2000, Le Toya and LaTavia were fired and replaced by Michelle Williams and Farrah Franklin. </p>

<p>They filed lawsuits against Mathew Knowles, Beyonce Knowles and Kelly Rowland, charging them with breach of partnership, among other claims. They eventually dropped their case against Beyonce and Kelly, and settled their case out against Mathew out of court.</p>

<p>Luckett went on to enjoy success as a solo artist, releasing the studio albums between 2006 and 2017. </p>

<p>The way they were: LeToya was part of Destiny's Child with Beyonce Knowles, Kelly Rowland and LaTavia Roberson, a group formed by Beyonce's dad Matthew Knowles in 1993.</p>
